* [A101107](https://oeis.org/A101107) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101107)): Sorted and uniqued list of class numbers (number of conjugacy classes) of all non-Abelian simple groups.

* [A101135](https://oeis.org/A101135) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101135)): a(1)=1. a(n) = a(n-1) + sum of the squares which are among the first (n-1) terms of the sequence.

* [A101157](https://oeis.org/A101157) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101157)): Let j be the smallest integer for which n+(n+1)+...+(n+j) is a square, say k^2; then a(n)=k.

* [A101160](https://oeis.org/A101160) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101160)): a(n) is the smallest integer j for which n+(n+1)+...+(n+j) is a square.
* [A101161](https://oeis.org/A101161) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101161)): A number triangle associated with the Chebyshev polynomials of the first kind.
* [A101162](https://oeis.org/A101162) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101162)): Row sums of a Chebyshev number triangle.
* [A101164](https://oeis.org/A101164) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101164)): Triangle read by rows: Delannoy numbers minus binomial coefficients.

* [A101169](https://oeis.org/A101169) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101169)): Lengths of successive words (starting with a) under the substitution: \{a -> aab, b -> aac, c -> ab\}.
* [A101184](https://oeis.org/A101184) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101184)): a(n) = n + pi(n) + pi(pi(n)) + pi(pi(pi(n))) + pi(pi(pi(pi(n)))) + ...
* [A101195](https://oeis.org/A101195) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101195)): Expansion of psi(x^3) / psi(x) in powers of x where psi() is a Ramanujan theta function.
* [A101197](https://oeis.org/A101197) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101197)): Lengths of successive words (starting with a) under the substitution: \{a -> aab, b -> aac, c -> b\}.
* [A101201](https://oeis.org/A101201) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101201)): Maximal number of kings in the toroidal king's graph on an n X n board such that each king is attacking no more than four other kings.
* [A101202](https://oeis.org/A101202) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101202)): Multiples of 142857.

* [A101256](https://oeis.org/A101256) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101256)): Sum of composites <= n.
* [A101257](https://oeis.org/A101257) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101257)): Remainder when the least divisor of n greater than or equal to the square root of n (A033677(n)) is divided by the greatest divisor of n less than or equal to the square root of n (A033676(n)).

* [A101265](https://oeis.org/A101265) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101265)): a(1) = 1, a(2) = 2, a(3) = 6; a(n) = 5\*a(n-1) - 5\*a(n-2) + a(n-3) for n>3.
* [A101266](https://oeis.org/A101266) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101266)): First differences of A101402.
* [A101269](https://oeis.org/A101269) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101269)): a(1)=0, a(2)=1 a(n+2)=(8\*n^2+2\*n+1)\*a(n+1)-2\*n\*(2\*n-1)^3\*a(n).

* [A101272](https://oeis.org/A101272) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101272)): a(n)=n, n <=6; a(n)=6, n > 6.
* [A101279](https://oeis.org/A101279) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101279)): a(1) = 1; a(2k) = a(k), a(2k+1) = k.

* [A101334](https://oeis.org/A101334) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101334)): a(n) = n^n - (n+1)^(n-1).

* [A101339](https://oeis.org/A101339) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101339)): Prime(n)^prime(n)-prime(n).
* [A101340](https://oeis.org/A101340) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101340)): a(n) = prime(n)^prime(n)+prime(n).

* [A101375](https://oeis.org/A101375) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101375)): a(n) = n\*(n+1)\*(n^2-2\*n+2)/2.

* [A101377](https://oeis.org/A101377) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101377)): a(n) = n^2\*(n^3-n+2)/2.
* [A101378](https://oeis.org/A101378) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101378)): a(n) = n^2\*(n^3+1)/2.
* [A101381](https://oeis.org/A101381) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101381)): a(n) = n^2\*(n+1)^2\*(4\*n^2 - 5\*n + 4)/12.
* [A101382](https://oeis.org/A101382) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101382)): a(n) = n\*(n+1)\*(2\*n^3 - n^2 + 2)^2/6.
* [A101383](https://oeis.org/A101383) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101383)): a(n) = n\*(n+1)\*(2\*n^3 - n^2 + 2)/6.
* [A101384](https://oeis.org/A101384) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101384)): a(n) = n\*(n-1)^3\*(n^2-n-1)/2.
* [A101386](https://oeis.org/A101386) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101386)): Expansion of g.f.: (5 - 3\*x)/(1 - 6\*x + x^2).
* [A101399](https://oeis.org/A101399) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101399)): a(0) = 1, a(1) = 2, a(2) = 5; for n >= 3, a(n) = a(n-1) + 2\*a(n-2) + a(n-3).
* [A101400](https://oeis.org/A101400) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101400)): a(n) = a(n-1) + 2\*a(n-2) + a(n-3) - a(n-4).

* [A101421](https://oeis.org/A101421) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101421)): Numbers which are the sum of two positive cubes and divisible by 7.
* [A101423](https://oeis.org/A101423) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101423)): Number of different cuboids with volume p^3 \* q^n, where p,q are distinct prime numbers.
* [A101424](https://oeis.org/A101424) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101424)): Number of different cuboids with volume p^4 \* q^n, where p,q are distinct prime numbers.
* [A101425](https://oeis.org/A101425) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101425)): Number of different cuboids with volume p^5 X q^n, where p,q are distinct prime numbers.
* [A101426](https://oeis.org/A101426) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101426)): Number of different cuboids with volume p^6 \* q^n, where p,q are distinct prime numbers.
* [A101427](https://oeis.org/A101427) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101427)): Number of different cuboids with volume (pq)^n, where p,q are distinct prime numbers.
* [A101428](https://oeis.org/A101428) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101428)): Number of ways to write n as an ordered sum of a triangular number (A000217) and a square (A000290).
* [A101432](https://oeis.org/A101432) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101432)): Each term is the number of letters in the Spanish name of the previous term.
* [A101433](https://oeis.org/A101433) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101433)): Partial sums of A101402.

* [A101441](https://oeis.org/A101441) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101441)): n^prime(n+1).
* [A101442](https://oeis.org/A101442) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101442)): a(n) = 9973\*n + 10007.

* [A101444](https://oeis.org/A101444) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101444)): Numbers k such that (9973\*k + 10007) is a prime.
* [A101447](https://oeis.org/A101447) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101447)): Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) = (2\*k+1)\*(n+1-k), 0 <= k < n.
* [A101448](https://oeis.org/A101448) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101448)): Nonnegative numbers k such that 2k + 11 is prime.

* [A101463](https://oeis.org/A101463) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101463)): G.f.: (x^3+x^2+2\*x+1)/(x^4+5\*x^2+1).
* [A101464](https://oeis.org/A101464) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101464)): Decimal expansion of sqrt(2-sqrt(2)), edge length of a regular octagon with circumradius 1.
* [A101465](https://oeis.org/A101465) ([program](/edit/?oeis=101465)): Decimal expansion of 2-sqrt(2), square of the edge length of a regular octagon with circumradius 1.

* [A119916](https://oeis.org/A119916) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119916)): Number of runs of 0's of odd length in all ternary words of length n.
* [A119917](https://oeis.org/A119917) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119917)): Number of rationals in [0, 1) consisting just of repeating bits of period at most n.
* [A119919](https://oeis.org/A119919) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119919)): Table read by antidiagonals: number of rationals in [0, 1) having at most n preperiodic bits, then at most k periodic bits (read up antidiagonals).
* [A119920](https://oeis.org/A119920) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119920)): Number of rationals in [0, 1) having exactly n preperiodic bits, then exactly n periodic bits.
* [A119921](https://oeis.org/A119921) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119921)): Number of rationals in [0, 1) having at most n preperiodic bits, then at most n periodic bits.
* [A119930](https://oeis.org/A119930) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119930)): Sum of the numbers of the matrix A111490 along a boustrophedon path: a11, a11+a12, a11+a12+a21, etc.
* [A119931](https://oeis.org/A119931) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119931)): Sum of the numbers of the matrix A111490 along a boustrophedon path: a11, a11+a21, a11+a21+a21, etc.
* [A119936](https://oeis.org/A119936) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119936)): Least common multiple (LCM) of denominators of the rows of the triangle of rationals A119935/A119932.
* [A119938](https://oeis.org/A119938) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119938)): Row sums of triangle A119937.
* [A119939](https://oeis.org/A119939) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119939)): Main diagonal of triangle A119937.
* [A119944](https://oeis.org/A119944) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119944)): First differences of A003418(n) = lcm(1..n).
* [A119951](https://oeis.org/A119951) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119951)): Numerators of partial sums of a convergent series with value 4, involving scaled Catalan numbers A000108.
* [A119956](https://oeis.org/A119956) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119956)): Numbers n such that n^3+1=p\*q\*r where p,q,r are distinct primes.
* [A119959](https://oeis.org/A119959) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119959)): p^2-p+1 central polygonal numbers with prime indices A002061(prime(n)).
* [A119963](https://oeis.org/A119963) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119963)): Triangle T(n,k), 0 <= k <= n, read by rows, with T(2n,2k) = T(2n+1,2k) = T(2n+1,2k+1) = T(2n+2,2k+1) = binomial(n,k).
* [A119967](https://oeis.org/A119967) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119967)): A transform of the central binomial coefficients C(n,floor(n/2)).
* [A119968](https://oeis.org/A119968) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119968)): Binomial transform of Fredholm-Rueppel sequence.
* [A119969](https://oeis.org/A119969) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119969)): Sum\{k>=0, C(2^k-1,n-2\*(2^k-1))\}.
* [A119970](https://oeis.org/A119970) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119970)): Binomial transform of A119969.
* [A119971](https://oeis.org/A119971) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119971)): G.f. sum\{k>=0, (x^2/(1-x)^3)^(2^k-1)\}.
* [A119972](https://oeis.org/A119972) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119972)): Flag n when the first difference of the decimal encoding of the Gray code is negative.
* [A119975](https://oeis.org/A119975) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119975)): E.g.f. exp(x)\*(Bessel\_I(0,2\*sqrt(2)x) + Bessel\_I(1,2\*sqrt(2)x)/sqrt(2)).
* [A119976](https://oeis.org/A119976) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119976)): E.g.f. exp(2x)\*(Bessel\_I(0,2\*sqrt(2)x) + Bessel\_I(1,2\*sqrt(2)x)/sqrt(2)).
* [A119979](https://oeis.org/A119979) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119979)): a(n+1)=(2^a(n) mod n)+1, with a(0)=1.
* [A119992](https://oeis.org/A119992) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119992)): a(n) = n-th positive integer which is coprime to n!.
* [A119993](https://oeis.org/A119993) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119993)): a(n) = n-th prime from among those primes which are coprime to n.
* [A119996](https://oeis.org/A119996) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119996)): Numerator of Sum\_\{k=1..n\} 1/(Fibonacci(k)\*Fibonacci(k+2)).
* [A119997](https://oeis.org/A119997) ([program](/edit/?oeis=119997)): Sum of all matrix elements of n X n matrix M[i,j] = (-1)^(i+j)\*Fibonacci[i+j-1].
* [A120007](https://oeis.org/A120007) ([program](/edit/?oeis=120007)): Mobius transform of sum of prime factors of n with multiplicity (A001414).
* [A120009](https://oeis.org/A120009) ([program](/edit/?oeis=120009)): G.f.: A(x) = (x-x^2) o x/(1-x) o (1-sqrt(1-4\*x))/2, a composition of functions involving the Catalan function and its inverse.
* [A120010](https://oeis.org/A120010) ([program](/edit/?oeis=120010)): G.f.: A(x) = (1-sqrt(1-4\*x))/2 o x/(1-x) o (x-x^2), a composition of functions involving the Catalan function and its inverse.
* [A120011](https://oeis.org/A120011) ([program](/edit/?oeis=120011)): Decimal expansion of sqrt(3)/4.

* [A120017](https://oeis.org/A120017) ([program](/edit/?oeis=120017)): The 2nd self-composition of A120010; g.f.: A(x) = G(G(x)), where G(x) = g.f. of A120010.
* [A120018](https://oeis.org/A120018) ([program](/edit/?oeis=120018)): The third self-composition of A120010; g.f.: A(x) = G(G(G(x))), where G(x) = g.f. of A120010.

* [A135317](https://oeis.org/A135317) ([program](/edit/?oeis=135317)): Sequence yielding an ordering of N\*N derived from a family of recurrences. For any integer k define h(k,1)=1 and for n>1 define h(k,n)=h(k,n-1)+2\*((-h(k,n-1)mod n)where "r mod s" denotes least nonnegative residue of r modulo s [informally, h(k,n) is got by "reflecting" h(k,n-1)in the least multiple of n that is >=h(k,n-1)]. Then for fixed k>=0 there are integers a(k), b(k), n(k) such that for all n>n(k) we have h(k,2\*n+1)-h(k,2\*n)=2\*a(k)and h(k,2\*n+2)-h(k,2\*n+1)=2\*b(k). For all k we have a(2\*k+1)=a(2\*k) and b(2\*k+1)=1+b(2\*k). Moreover b(2\*k) is even for all k. The function k->(a(2\*k),b(2\*k)/2) is a bijection from the nonnegative integers N to N\*N. It is "monotone" in the sense that k<=k' whenever a(2\*k)<=a(2\*k') and b(2\*k)<=b(2\*k'). The sequence given above is a(2\*k).
